Package: perturbatr
Type: Package
Title: Statistical Analysis of High-Throughput Genetic Perturbation Screens
Version: 0.99.5
Date: 2018-02-1
Authors@R: person("Simon", "Dirmeier",
	email = "simon.dirmeier@web.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Simon Dirmeier <simon.dirmeier@web.de>
Description: perturbatr does statistical analysis of large-scale genetic
  perturbation screens using a random effects model and network diffusion.
  perturbatr analyses dat sets from single perturbation experiments and
  multiple integrated data sets alike by modelling the different biological
  conditions using random effects. The random effects model computes
  pan-screen gene effects for all genes, e.g. effect sizes for genes over all
  screens. In order to account for possible false negatives, we employ network
  diffusion by mapping the gene effects onto a genetic network and smoothing
  the estimated effects over the edges of the network.
